MOST IMMEDIATE
No.1/34/1/2016-Cab.
GOVERNMENT OF INDIA (BHARAT SARKAR)
CABINET SECRETARIAT (MANTRIMANDAL SACHIVALAYA)
New Delhi, the 5th July, 2016
The undersigned is directed to say that with effect from the 5th July, 2016:
Shri Arun Jaitley, relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of Information and
Broadcasting. He will continue to hold the charge of the office
Minister of Corporate Affairs.
Shri M. Venkaiah Naidu relingquished the charge of the office of the Minister of Parliamentary
Affairs, and assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of Informațion and
Broadcasting. He will continue to hold the charge of the office of the Minister of Urban
Development; and Minister of Housing and Urban Poverty Alleviation.
Shri D.V. Sadananda Gowda relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of Law and
Justice, and assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of Statistics and Programme
·Implementation.
Shri Ananthkumar, Minister of Chemicals and Fertilizers also assumed the charge of the
office of the Minister of Parliamentary Affairs.
Shri Ravi Shankar Prasad relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of
Communications and Information Technology. He assumed the charge of the office of the
Minister of Law and Justice; and Minister of Electronics and Information Technology.
Shri Narendra Singh Tomar relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of Mines
and Minister of Steel and assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of Rural
Development; Minister of Panchayati Raj; and Minister of Drinking Water and Sanitation.
Shri Chaudhary Birender Singh relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of Rural
Development; Minister of Panchayati Raj; and Minister of Drinking Water and Sanitation,
and assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of Steel.
Smt. Smriti Zubin Irani relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of Human
Resource Development, and assumed the charge of the office of the Ministry of Textiles.
Shri Prakash Javadekar relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of State
(Independent Charge) of the Ministry of Environment, Forest and Climate Change, and
assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of Human Resource Development.
Rao Inderjit Singh relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of State in the
Ministry of Defence, and assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of State in the
Ministry of Urban Development; and Ministry of Housing and Urban Poverty Alleviation. He
will continue hold the charge of the office of the Minister of State (Independent Charge) of
the Ministry of Planning.
Shri Rajiv Pratap Rudy relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of State in the
Ministry of Parliamentary Affairs. He will continue to hold the charge of the office of the
Minister of State (Independent Charge) of the Ministry of Skill Development and
Entrepreneurship.
Shri Vijay Goel assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of State (Independent
Charge) of the Ministry of Youth Affairs and Sports; and the office of the Minister of State in
the Ministry of Water Resources, River Development and Ganga Rejuvenation.
Shri Shripad Yesso Naik relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of State in the
Ministry of Health and Family Welfare. He will continue to hold the charge of the office of
.the Minister of State (Independent Charge) of the Ministry of Ayurveda, Yoga and
Naturopathy, Unani, Siddha and Homoeopathy (AYUSH).
Shri Piyush Goyal, Minister of State (Independent Charge) of the Ministry of Power; Minister
of State (Independent Charge) of the Ministry of Coal; and Minister of State (Independent
Charge) of the Ministry of New and Renewable Energy, also assumed the charge of the
office of the Minister of State (Independent Charge) of the Ministry of Mines.
Dr. Jitendra Singh relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of State (Independent
Charge) of the Ministry of Youth Affairs and Sports. He will continue to hold the charge of
the office of the Minister of State (Independent Charge) of the Ministry of Development of
North Eastern Region; Minister of State in the Prime Minister's Office; Minister of State in the
Ministry of Personnel, Public Grievances and Pensions; Minister of State in the Department
of Atomic Energy; and Minister of State in the Department of Space.
Dr. Mahesh Sharma relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of State in the
Ministry of Civil Aviation. He will continue to hold the charge of the office of the Minister of
State (Independent Charge) of the Ministry of Culture; and Minister of State (Independent
Charge) of the Ministry of Tourism.
